Madison Avenue, east side, from 122nd to 123rd Streets, showing brownstone fronts and a glimpse of the Hospital for Joint Diseases. July 24, 1932.

P. L. Sperr, Photographer.

Madison Avenue, east side, south from E. 123rd (left of view 1) to 120th (right of View 3) Streets, showing several blocks of brown stone dwellings facing on Mount Morris Park. View No. 1 shows the 123rd to 122nd Street block; No. 2 an extensive view southward from 122nd Street; and No. 3, the 121st to 120th Street block. Shown at the N.E. corner of this thoroughfare and E. 121st Street is the Russian Orthodox Church of Christ the Saviour. Upon this site formerly stood a one story structure listed in Bromleys Atlas of New York of 1922 as the property of the Knights of Columbus.

August 24, 1938.
Views 1,2 and 3.

P.L. Sperr
